{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GsxFTdnusREzqhYRYQdp1A","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent. Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the comprehensive report for the user.\n\n## Title Extractor Codebase Structure Report\n\nBased on my analysis of the codebase, here are the key files and components:\n\n### **Primary File**\n- **Absolute Path**: `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`\n\n---\n\n## **Key Constants and Line Numbers**\n\n### METADATA_PATTERNS\n- **Lines 51-76**: Regex patterns identifying recipe metadata (serving sizes, prep/cook times, schedule info, Polish variations, category indicators)\n  - Includes both English and OCR-resilient Polish patterns\n  - Examples: `SERVES`, `COOK TIME`, `DLA OSÓB`, `SEZON`, `CZĘŚĆ`\n\n### SECTION_LABELS\n- **Lines 112-164**: Set of ~60 known recipe section labels in English and Polish\n  - English: \"ingredients\", \"directions\", \"instructions\", \"method\", \"garnish\", \"frosting\", \"filling\", etc.\n  - Polish (without diacritics): \"skladniki\", \"przygotowanie\", \"sposob przygotowania\", \"warzywa\", \"zupy\", \"desery\", etc.\n  - Also includes recipe-book chapter labels\n\n### COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS\n- **Line 268**: Regex pattern matching English cooking instruction imperative verbs\n  - Pattern: `^(beat|fold|stir|mix|add|pour|bake|cook|cool|remove|place|combine|whisk|knead|roll|spread|brush|slice|chop|dice|mince|drain|rinse|peel|grate|melt|simmer|boil|fry|sauté|saute|roast|grill|broil|steam|let|set|transfer|serve|garnish|arrange|sprinkle|season|preheat|cover|uncover|reduce|bring|toss|cut|trim|shape|form)\\b/i`\n\n### POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS\n- **Line 275**: OCR-resilient Polish cooking instruction verbs\n  - Includes ~40+ Polish imperative forms with diacritic alternatives\n  - Examples: \"podawaj\", \"dodaj\", \"smaż\", \"gotuj\", \"pokrój\", etc.\n\n### MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS\n- **Lines 20-46**: List of ~40 cooking units in English and Polish\n  - English: \"cup\", \"tbsp\", \"gram\", \"ml\", \"liter\", \"pinch\", \"dash\", \"handful\"\n  - Polish: \"łyżka\", \"łyżeczka\", \"szklanka\", \"szczypta\", \"garść\", etc.\n\n### Reference Embeddings\n- **Lines 10-15**: Three semantic reference strings for title extraction:\n  - `TITLE_REFERENCE`: \"recipe name, dish title, name of the food, nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\"\n  - `HEADER_REFERENCE`: \"ingredients list, cooking directions, section heading, składniki, przygotowanie, sposób wykonania\"\n  - `NOISE_REFERENCE`: \"page number, table of contents, book footer, garbled text\"\n\n---\n\n## **Key Functions with Line Numbers**\n\n### isLikelyGarbled()\n- **Lines 206-265**\n- Detects OCR noise and garbled text using:\n  - Vowel ratio check (30-50% expected for English/Polish)\n  - Single orphaned short words (≤3 letters)\n  - Internal case transitions (e.g., \"UuIw\")\n  - Lowercase starting letters (recipe titles always start uppercase)\n  - Mid-text sentence boundaries (\". \" followed by letter = body text)\n  - Multi-word fragments with garbled short words\n\n### passesHardFilters()\n- **Lines 285-326**\n- Hard reject filters:\n  - **Length checks**: `text.length < 3 || text.length > 80` (rejects too short or too long)\n  - **8-word limit**: `words.length >= 8 && !/ [+:&/] /.test(text)` (exception for compound titles with separators)\n  - Ingredient-like lines\n  - Lines starting with numbers\n  - Metadata lines\n  - Garbled text\n  - Cooking instructions\n  - Pipe-separated lines (navigation headers)\n  - Bullet-list items\n  - Sub-section headers (lines ending with \":\" except compound separators)\n  - Page references, corruption annotations, bracket categories\n  - Section labels\n  - Single-word non-title fragments\n\n### normalizeOcrTitle()\n- **Lines 609-659**\n- **Step 1** (lines 612-617): Strips trailing section markers like \"+ SERVING AND STORAGE\"\n- **Step 2** (lines 619-650): OCR character substitution (ALL_CAPS: 1→I, 0→O, 4→A, 5→S, etc.)\n- **Step 3** (lines 652-656): Title-case conversion ONLY when OCR substitution actually changed text (preserves clean ALL_CAPS titles)\n\n### buildCandidates()\n- **Lines 418-581**\n- Builds candidate titles from single and multi-line joins:\n  1. Detects and skips burst of initial garbled lines using `findBurstEnd()` (lines 332-387)\n  2. Pre-joins hyphen-broken lines (lines 434-440)\n  3. Pre-merges consecutive short ALL_CAPS lines (lines 442-484)\n  4. Pre-merges continuation lines starting with `/&+:(`  (lines 486-504)\n  5. Generates single-line candidates (lines 520-534)\n  6. Generates 2-line join candidates with section-label blocking logic (lines 538-548)\n  7. Generates 3-line join candidates with section-label blocking logic (lines 552-563)\n  8. Pre-filters to top 25 by ALL_CAPS priority, then word count (lines 568-577)\n\n### extractTitleWithEmbeddings()\n- **Lines 672-1148**: Main extraction function with multi-stage scoring and dedup logic\n\n#### **Position Factor Calculation** (Lines 772-776)\n```typescript\nconst relativePosition = rs.position / lines.length;\nconst positionFactor = relativePosition < 0.5\n  ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - relativePosition * 2)\n  : 1.0;\n```\n- Multiplicative bonus for early-position candidates (max +12% at position 0)\n- No bonus for position > 50% of document\n\n#### **Scoring Logic** (Lines 770-795)\n- `rawScore`: embedding quality (titleSim - max(headerSim, noiseSim))\n- `allCapsBonus`: +0.08 for multi-word ALL_CAPS (≥2 words, ≥4 letters each), +0.03 for single-word ALL_CAPS\n- `structuralBonus`: +0.10 for best ALL_CAPS structural heading\n- `score`: `rawScore * positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus`\n- `thresholdScore`: excludes structuralBonus to prevent threshold inflation\n\n#### **Threshold Calculation** (Lines 903-909)\n```typescript\nconst bestThresholdScore = Math.max(...scoredForThreshold.map((s) => s.thresholdScore));\nconst threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7);\nlet selected = scoredForThreshold.filter((s) => s.score >= threshold);\n```\n- Dynamic threshold: max of 0.08 or 70% of best thresholdScore\n\n#### **Bilingual Title Detection** (Lines 801-856)\n- Detects mixed-case title at position 0 followed by ALL_CAPS at position 1-2\n- Uses two methods:\n  1. **Embedding similarity** (>0.4 cosine similarity)\n  2. **Layout-based** (≥2 words each, no word overlap)\n- Suppresses identified translations before threshold calculation\n\n#### **Dedup Logic** (Lines 1039-1052)\n```typescript\nselected = selected.filter((a) => {\n  const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n  return !selected.some(\n    (b) =>\n      b !== a &&\n      aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n      b.text.length < a.text.length\n  );\n});\n```\n- **Rule: Shorter wins** — if one title is substring of another, keep the shorter (more focused) one\n- **Critical note** (line 1040): \"DO NOT CHANGE THIS LOGIC — it has been incorrectly 'improved' 5 times\"\n- Pre-filtering above handles edge cases (structural heading prefix removal) so incomplete prefixes don't appear here\n\n#### **Multi-title and Continuation Protection** (Lines 944-976, 1001-1019)\n- **Continuation joins protection** (lines 944-976): Protects 2/3-line joins from having their prefixes/suffixes removed by dedup when join starts with `/&+:(`\n- **Component single removal** (lines 1001-1019): When multi-line join survives, removes its component single-word parts if ≥2 components also survived\n- **Structural heading prefix removal** (lines 927-942): Removes word-boundary prefixes of structural headings when the complete heading survived\n\n#### **Multi-recipe Page Logic** (Lines 1061-1123)\n- **≥2 ALL_CAPS headings**: Check if non-first headings are sub-headers (followed by ingredients) or separate recipes\n  - If sub-headers: collapse to first ALL_CAPS only\n  - If separate recipes: keep all ALL_CAPS candidates\n- **1 ALL_CAPS heading**: Check if it's in last 25% of document (likely category footer); if so, prefer earlier candidates\n- **0 ALL_CAPS (mixed-case page)**: If candidates span >10 lines (body-text leakage), collapse to highest-scoring candidate within 3 positions of earliest; otherwise keep all\n\n#### **Final Selection** (Lines 1125-1147)\n- Cap at 3 candidates, sort by position\n- Join with \" + \" separator\n- Fallback (lines 1129-1142): If threshold eliminated all candidates, return earliest positional candidate if rawScore > -0.5\n- Normalize via `normalizeOcrTitle()` before returning\n\n---\n\n## **Related Files**\n\n### Labels File (for reference only)\n- **Absolute Path**: `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/labels.ts`\n- Contains `SEASON_LABELS` and `CUISINE_LABELS` constants (not used in title extraction)\n\n---\n\n## **Critical Edge Cases Handled**\n\n1. **OCR-fragmented headings**: Pre-merged if 2+ ALL_CAPS lines with ≤2 words and ≤25 chars\n2. **Hyphen-broken lines**: Pre-joined before candidate generation\n3. **Continuation lines**: Pre-merged if next line starts with `/&+:(`\n4. **Bilingual pages**: Detects and suppresses translation candidates\n5. **Multi-recipe pages**: Distinguishes multi-recipe titles from sub-section headers based on ingredient context\n6. **Garbled structural headings**: Hard disqualifies truncated ALL_CAPS (e.g., \"FRON\" when \"SAFFRON\" exists)\n7. **Metadata continuation**: Skips short ALL_CAPS fragments immediately following metadata lines\n8. **Position-0 compound protection**: Removes distant sub-section headers that would destroy position-0 compound titles via dedup"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a4e740c9d3ce1c35b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 114192\ntool_uses: 19\nduration_ms: 69343</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"992d880b-e463-4199-be8a-c9ca68db2e09","uuid":"5436f3f8-2416-4b04-8986-14b323dd4041","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the structure of the title extractor codebase. Find and read the key files:\n\n1. lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts - especially the functions: normalizeOcrTitle, passesHardFilters, isLikelyGarbled, buildCandidates, extractTitleWithEmbeddings, and the dedup logic. Note the line numbers of each.\n2. Any existing SECTION_LABELS, METADATA_PATTERNS, COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS constants\n3. lib/text-classifier/food-dictionary.ts (if it exists)\n\nReport back with:\n- File paths (absolute)\n- Line numbers for each key function and constant\n- The current dedup logic code\n- The current position factor calculation code\n- The current normalizeOcrTitle function\n- The current isLikelyGarbled function\n- The current passesHardFilters function (especially the 8-word and length checks)\n- The COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS list","agentId":"a4e740c9d3ce1c35b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent. Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the comprehensive report for the user.\n\n## Title Extractor Codebase Structure Report\n\nBased on my analysis of the codebase, here are the key files and components:\n\n### **Primary File**\n- **Absolute Path**: `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`\n\n---\n\n## **Key Constants and Line Numbers**\n\n### METADATA_PATTERNS\n- **Lines 51-76**: Regex patterns identifying recipe metadata (serving sizes, prep/cook times, schedule info, Polish variations, category indicators)\n  - Includes both English and OCR-resilient Polish patterns\n  - Examples: `SERVES`, `COOK TIME`, `DLA OSÓB`, `SEZON`, `CZĘŚĆ`\n\n### SECTION_LABELS\n- **Lines 112-164**: Set of ~60 known recipe section labels in English and Polish\n  - English: \"ingredients\", \"directions\", \"instructions\", \"method\", \"garnish\", \"frosting\", \"filling\", etc.\n  - Polish (without diacritics): \"skladniki\", \"przygotowanie\", \"sposob przygotowania\", \"warzywa\", \"zupy\", \"desery\", etc.\n  - Also includes recipe-book chapter labels\n\n### COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS\n- **Line 268**: Regex pattern matching English cooking instruction imperative verbs\n  - Pattern: `^(beat|fold|stir|mix|add|pour|bake|cook|cool|remove|place|combine|whisk|knead|roll|spread|brush|slice|chop|dice|mince|drain|rinse|peel|grate|melt|simmer|boil|fry|sauté|saute|roast|grill|broil|steam|let|set|transfer|serve|garnish|arrange|sprinkle|season|preheat|cover|uncover|reduce|bring|toss|cut|trim|shape|form)\\b/i`\n\n### POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS\n- **Line 275**: OCR-resilient Polish cooking instruction verbs\n  - Includes ~40+ Polish imperative forms with diacritic alternatives\n  - Examples: \"podawaj\", \"dodaj\", \"smaż\", \"gotuj\", \"pokrój\", etc.\n\n### MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS\n- **Lines 20-46**: List of ~40 cooking units in English and Polish\n  - English: \"cup\", \"tbsp\", \"gram\", \"ml\", \"liter\", \"pinch\", \"dash\", \"handful\"\n  - Polish: \"łyżka\", \"łyżeczka\", \"szklanka\", \"szczypta\", \"garść\", etc.\n\n### Reference Embeddings\n- **Lines 10-15**: Three semantic reference strings for title extraction:\n  - `TITLE_REFERENCE`: \"recipe name, dish title, name of the food, nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\"\n  - `HEADER_REFERENCE`: \"ingredients list, cooking directions, section heading, składniki, przygotowanie, sposób wykonania\"\n  - `NOISE_REFERENCE`: \"page number, table of contents, book footer, garbled text\"\n\n---\n\n## **Key Functions with Line Numbers**\n\n### isLikelyGarbled()\n- **Lines 206-265**\n- Detects OCR noise and garbled text using:\n  - Vowel ratio check (30-50% expected for English/Polish)\n  - Single orphaned short words (≤3 letters)\n  - Internal case transitions (e.g., \"UuIw\")\n  - Lowercase starting letters (recipe titles always start uppercase)\n  - Mid-text sentence boundaries (\". \" followed by letter = body text)\n  - Multi-word fragments with garbled short words\n\n### passesHardFilters()\n- **Lines 285-326**\n- Hard reject filters:\n  - **Length checks**: `text.length < 3 || text.length > 80` (rejects too short or too long)\n  - **8-word limit**: `words.length >= 8 && !/ [+:&/] /.test(text)` (exception for compound titles with separators)\n  - Ingredient-like lines\n  - Lines starting with numbers\n  - Metadata lines\n  - Garbled text\n  - Cooking instructions\n  - Pipe-separated lines (navigation headers)\n  - Bullet-list items\n  - Sub-section headers (lines ending with \":\" except compound separators)\n  - Page references, corruption annotations, bracket categories\n  - Section labels\n  - Single-word non-title fragments\n\n### normalizeOcrTitle()\n- **Lines 609-659**\n- **Step 1** (lines 612-617): Strips trailing section markers like \"+ SERVING AND STORAGE\"\n- **Step 2** (lines 619-650): OCR character substitution (ALL_CAPS: 1→I, 0→O, 4→A, 5→S, etc.)\n- **Step 3** (lines 652-656): Title-case conversion ONLY when OCR substitution actually changed text (preserves clean ALL_CAPS titles)\n\n### buildCandidates()\n- **Lines 418-581**\n- Builds candidate titles from single and multi-line joins:\n  1. Detects and skips burst of initial garbled lines using `findBurstEnd()` (lines 332-387)\n  2. Pre-joins hyphen-broken lines (lines 434-440)\n  3. Pre-merges consecutive short ALL_CAPS lines (lines 442-484)\n  4. Pre-merges continuation lines starting with `/&+:(`  (lines 486-504)\n  5. Generates single-line candidates (lines 520-534)\n  6. Generates 2-line join candidates with section-label blocking logic (lines 538-548)\n  7. Generates 3-line join candidates with section-label blocking logic (lines 552-563)\n  8. Pre-filters to top 25 by ALL_CAPS priority, then word count (lines 568-577)\n\n### extractTitleWithEmbeddings()\n- **Lines 672-1148**: Main extraction function with multi-stage scoring and dedup logic\n\n#### **Position Factor Calculation** (Lines 772-776)\n```typescript\nconst relativePosition = rs.position / lines.length;\nconst positionFactor = relativePosition < 0.5\n  ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - relativePosition * 2)\n  : 1.0;\n```\n- Multiplicative bonus for early-position candidates (max +12% at position 0)\n- No bonus for position > 50% of document\n\n#### **Scoring Logic** (Lines 770-795)\n- `rawScore`: embedding quality (titleSim - max(headerSim, noiseSim))\n- `allCapsBonus`: +0.08 for multi-word ALL_CAPS (≥2 words, ≥4 letters each), +0.03 for single-word ALL_CAPS\n- `structuralBonus`: +0.10 for best ALL_CAPS structural heading\n- `score`: `rawScore * positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus`\n- `thresholdScore`: excludes structuralBonus to prevent threshold inflation\n\n#### **Threshold Calculation** (Lines 903-909)\n```typescript\nconst bestThresholdScore = Math.max(...scoredForThreshold.map((s) => s.thresholdScore));\nconst threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7);\nlet selected = scoredForThreshold.filter((s) => s.score >= threshold);\n```\n- Dynamic threshold: max of 0.08 or 70% of best thresholdScore\n\n#### **Bilingual Title Detection** (Lines 801-856)\n- Detects mixed-case title at position 0 followed by ALL_CAPS at position 1-2\n- Uses two methods:\n  1. **Embedding similarity** (>0.4 cosine similarity)\n  2. **Layout-based** (≥2 words each, no word overlap)\n- Suppresses identified translations before threshold calculation\n\n#### **Dedup Logic** (Lines 1039-1052)\n```typescript\nselected = selected.filter((a) => {\n  const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n  return !selected.some(\n    (b) =>\n      b !== a &&\n      aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n      b.text.length < a.text.length\n  );\n});\n```\n- **Rule: Shorter wins** — if one title is substring of another, keep the shorter (more focused) one\n- **Critical note** (line 1040): \"DO NOT CHANGE THIS LOGIC — it has been incorrectly 'improved' 5 times\"\n- Pre-filtering above handles edge cases (structural heading prefix removal) so incomplete prefixes don't appear here\n\n#### **Multi-title and Continuation Protection** (Lines 944-976, 1001-1019)\n- **Continuation joins protection** (lines 944-976): Protects 2/3-line joins from having their prefixes/suffixes removed by dedup when join starts with `/&+:(`\n- **Component single removal** (lines 1001-1019): When multi-line join survives, removes its component single-word parts if ≥2 components also survived\n- **Structural heading prefix removal** (lines 927-942): Removes word-boundary prefixes of structural headings when the complete heading survived\n\n#### **Multi-recipe Page Logic** (Lines 1061-1123)\n- **≥2 ALL_CAPS headings**: Check if non-first headings are sub-headers (followed by ingredients) or separate recipes\n  - If sub-headers: collapse to first ALL_CAPS only\n  - If separate recipes: keep all ALL_CAPS candidates\n- **1 ALL_CAPS heading**: Check if it's in last 25% of document (likely category footer); if so, prefer earlier candidates\n- **0 ALL_CAPS (mixed-case page)**: If candidates span >10 lines (body-text leakage), collapse to highest-scoring candidate within 3 positions of earliest; otherwise keep all\n\n#### **Final Selection** (Lines 1125-1147)\n- Cap at 3 candidates, sort by position\n- Join with \" + \" separator\n- Fallback (lines 1129-1142): If threshold eliminated all candidates, return earliest positional candidate if rawScore > -0.5\n- Normalize via `normalizeOcrTitle()` before returning\n\n---\n\n## **Related Files**\n\n### Labels File (for reference only)\n- **Absolute Path**: `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/labels.ts`\n- Contains `SEASON_LABELS` and `CUISINE_LABELS` constants (not used in title extraction)\n\n---\n\n## **Critical Edge Cases Handled**\n\n1. **OCR-fragmented headings**: Pre-merged if 2+ ALL_CAPS lines with ≤2 words and ≤25 chars\n2. **Hyphen-broken lines**: Pre-joined before candidate generation\n3. **Continuation lines**: Pre-merged if next line starts with `/&+:(`\n4. **Bilingual pages**: Detects and suppresses translation candidates\n5. **Multi-recipe pages**: Distinguishes multi-recipe titles from sub-section headers based on ingredient context\n6. **Garbled structural headings**: Hard disqualifies truncated ALL_CAPS (e.g., \"FRON\" when \"SAFFRON\" exists)\n7. **Metadata continuation**: Skips short ALL_CAPS fragments immediately following metadata lines\n8. **Position-0 compound protection**: Removes distant sub-section headers that would destroy position-0 compound titles via dedup"}],"totalDurationMs":69343,"totalTokens":114192,"totalToolUseCount":19,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3359,"cache_read_input_tokens":107999,"output_tokens":2834,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3359},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
