{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016UFyj9patZBJwYF7H7ahXM","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/24-b15aa30/tasks/task-01.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"992d880b-e463-4199-be8a-c9ca68db2e09","uuid":"1dfff3be-0df6-48ec-abf5-bbc7a38b3796","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/24-b15aa30/tasks/task-01.md","content":"# Task 01: Create food-word dictionary for OCR repair\n\n## Summary\n\nCreate a new file with a Set of ~500 common English and Polish food/cooking words used for dictionary-guided OCR repair.\n\n## Files to modify\n\n- **New file**: `lib/text-classifier/food-dictionary.ts`\n\n## Changes\n\nCreate `lib/text-classifier/food-dictionary.ts` exporting a `Set<string>` of lowercase food and cooking words. Words should be stored **without diacritics** (for OCR-resilient matching — OCR often strips diacritics). The set should include:\n\n### English (~250 words)\n\nIngredients: chicken, beef, pork, lamb, salmon, cod, halibut, shrimp, tofu, rice, pasta, bread, butter, cream, cheese, garlic, onion, tomato, potato, carrot, celery, pepper, salt, sugar, flour, egg, milk, oil, vinegar, lemon, lime, orange, apple, berry, blackberry, blueberry, raspberry, strawberry, cherry, peach, pear, plum, grape, banana, mango, pineapple, coconut, almond, walnut, pecan, cashew, pistachio, hazelnut, peanut, sesame, ginger, cinnamon, cumin, paprika, turmeric, oregano, basil, thyme, rosemary, parsley, cilantro, dill, mint, sage, chive, tarragon, nutmeg, clove, cardamom, saffron, vanilla, chocolate, cocoa, honey, maple, molasses, arugula, spinach, kale, lettuce, cabbage, broccoli, cauliflower, asparagus, artichoke, eggplant, zucchini, squash, pumpkin, cucumber, radish, turnip, beet, mushroom, avocado, olive, corn, bean, lentil, chickpea, quinoa, oat, barley, wheat, rye, ...\n\nCooking terms: bake, roast, grill, fry, saute, braise, simmer, boil, steam, poach, broil, smoke, cure, pickle, ferment, blanch, reduce, deglaze, emulsify, whisk, knead, fold, chop, dice, mince, slice, julienne, marinate, season, glaze, caramelize, sear, flambe, ...\n\nDish types: salad, soup, stew, casserole, risotto, curry, pie, tart, cake, cookie, brownie, muffin, scone, pancake, waffle, crepe, quiche, frittata, omelette, sandwich, wrap, burger, pizza, pasta, noodle, dumpling, pierogi, sushi, taco, burrito, enchilada, ...\n\n### Polish (~250 words)\n\nIngredients (without diacritics): kurczak, wolowina, wieprzowina, cielecina, golonka, losos, dorsz, krewetki, ryz, makaron, chleb, maslo, smietana, ser, czosnek, cebula, pomidor, ziemniak, marchew, seler, pieprz, sol, cukier, maka, jajko, mleko, olej, ocet, cytryna, pomarancza, jablko, jagoda, malina, truskawka, wisnia, brzoskwinia, gruszka, sliwka, winogrono, banan, orzech, migdal, imbir, cynamon, kminek, papryka, kurkuma, oregano, bazylia, tymianek, rozmaryn, pietruszka, kolendra, koperek, mieta, szalwia, szpinak, kapusta, brukselka, kalafior, szparag, baklazan, cukinia, dynia, ogorek, rzodkiewka, burak, grzyb, awokado, oliwka, fasola, soczewica, ciecierzyca, kasza, owies, jeczmien, pszenica, zyto, sernik, piernik, placki, nalesniki, bigos, zurek, barszcz, rosol, kotlet, schabowy, golabki, ...\n\nCooking terms (without diacritics): piec, smazyc, grillowac, gotowac, dusic, blanszowac, kroic, siekac, marynowac, przyprawiac, karmelizowac, ...\n\nSection labels that look like food words after OCR but are NOT titles (store separately or annotate): skladniki (ingredients), przygotowanie (preparation), sposob (method), wykonanie (execution), porcje (servings), ...\n\n### Export\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * ~500 common English and Polish food/cooking words for OCR repair.\n * Words are lowercase, without diacritics (OCR-resilient matching).\n * Used by repairOcrWord() to resolve ambiguous digit→letter substitutions.\n */\nexport const FOOD_DICTIONARY: Set<string> = new Set([\n  // English ingredients\n  \"chicken\", \"beef\", \"pork\", \"lamb\", \"salmon\", \"cod\", \"halibut\",\n  // ... all words ...\n]);\n```\n\n### Important details\n\n- Store all words lowercase, without diacritics (e.g., \"chleb\" not \"Chleb\", \"zolty\" not \"żółty\")\n- Include common compound-word parts: \"roasted\", \"grilled\", \"braised\", \"baked\", \"fried\", \"steamed\", \"smoked\", \"stuffed\", \"glazed\", \"caramelized\"\n- Include words that appear in the test failures: \"arugula\", \"salad\", \"blackberry\", \"fool\", \"chleb\", \"pszenny\", \"razowy\", \"grilled\", \"herb\", \"lemon\"\n- Include \"wine\", \"white\", \"red\", \"green\", \"black\", \"brown\", \"sweet\", \"sour\", \"hot\", \"cold\", \"fresh\", \"dried\", \"whole\", \"ground\" (common recipe adjectives that may appear in titles)\n- The dictionary does NOT need to be exhaustive — it's a positive signal for disambiguation, not a filter\n\n## Verification\n\n1. File exists at `lib/text-classifier/food-dictionary.ts`\n2. TypeScript compiles without errors: `npx tsc --noEmit lib/text-classifier/food-dictionary.ts`\n3. Dictionary contains at least 400 words\n4. All words are lowercase\n5. Key test words are present: \"arugula\", \"salad\", \"blackberry\", \"chleb\", \"pszenny\", \"grilled\", \"chicken\", \"piernik\", \"placki\", \"ziemniaczane\", \"sernik\"\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
