{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Q8HncupWuzhgDKVNbZsEUA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JpWNkrgq83gXGRe8XJVZXq","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/24-b15aa30/tasks/task-02.md","content":"# Task 02: Add dictionary-guided OCR repair function\n\n## Summary\n\nAdd a `repairOcrWord()` function to title-extractor.ts that uses the food dictionary to resolve ambiguous digit-to-letter substitutions in OCR-corrupted words.\n\n## Files to modify\n\n- `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Task 01 (food-dictionary.ts must exist)\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. Import the food dictionary\n\nAt the top of `title-extractor.ts`, add:\n\n```typescript\nimport { FOOD_DICTIONARY } from \"./food-dictionary\";\n```\n\n### 2. Add the `repairOcrWord()` function\n\nAdd a new function (place it near `normalizeOcrTitle`, around line 608):\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * OCR digit→letter substitution map.\n * Each key is a character that OCR commonly confuses; values are possible correct letters.\n */\nconst OCR_SUBSTITUTIONS: Record<string, string[]> = {\n  \"0\": [\"o\"],\n  \"1\": [\"i\", \"l\"],\n  \"4\": [\"a\"],\n  \"5\": [\"s\"],\n  \"¡\": [\"i\"],\n  \"Í\": [\"i\"],\n  \"€\": [\"e\"],\n};\n\nconst OCR_ARTIFACT_PATTERN = /[0-9¡Í€]/;\n\n/**\n * Attempt to repair a single OCR-corrupted word using dictionary lookup.\n * Returns the repaired word if a dictionary match is found, otherwise returns the original.\n *\n * Strategy: enumerate all possible digit→letter substitutions and check if any\n * produces a dictionary match. For efficiency, only runs when the word contains\n * a known OCR artifact character.\n */\nfunction repairOcrWord(word: string): string {\n  if (!OCR_ARTIFACT_PATTERN.test(word)) return word;\n\n  const lower = word.toLowerCase();\n\n  // Find positions of OCR artifact characters\n  const positions: { index: number; replacements: string[] }[] = [];\n  for (let i = 0; i < lower.length; i++) {\n    const replacements = OCR_SUBSTITUTIONS[lower[i]];\n    if (replacements) {\n      positions.push({ index: i, replacements });\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (positions.length === 0 || positions.length > 8) return word;\n\n  // Generate all substitution combinations\n  const candidates = generateSubstitutions(lower, positions, 0);\n\n  for (const candidate of candidates) {\n    if (FOOD_DICTIONARY.has(candidate)) {\n      // Preserve original casing pattern: if original was ALL_CAPS, return ALL_CAPS\n      if (word === word.toUpperCase()) return candidate.toUpperCase();\n      // If original was Title Case, return Title Case\n      if (word[0] === word[0].toUpperCase()) {\n        return candidate[0].toUpperCase() + candidate.slice(1);\n      }\n      return candidate;\n    }\n  }\n\n  return word; // No dictionary match — return original unchanged\n}\n\n/**\n * Recursively generate all substitution variants for OCR artifact positions.\n */\nfunction generateSubstitutions(\n  base: string,\n  positions: { index: number; replacements: string[] }[],\n  posIdx: number,\n): string[] {\n  if (posIdx >= positions.length) return [base];\n\n  const { index, replacements } = positions[posIdx];\n  const results: string[] = [];\n\n  for (const replacement of replacements) {\n    const variant = base.slice(0, index) + replacement + base.slice(index + 1);\n    results.push(...generateSubstitutions(variant, positions, posIdx + 1));\n  }\n\n  return results;\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Add a `repairOcrText()` helper for full lines\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * Apply dictionary-guided OCR repair to all words in a text string.\n * Only modifies words that contain OCR artifact characters AND have a dictionary match.\n */\nfunction repairOcrText(text: string): string {\n  return text\n    .split(/\\s+/)\n    .map((word) => {\n      // Strip punctuation for dictionary lookup, but preserve it in output\n      const match = word.match(/^([^a-zA-Z0-9À-ÿ]*)(.*?)([^a-zA-Z0-9À-ÿ]*)$/);\n      if (!match) return word;\n      const [, prefix, core, suffix] = match;\n      if (!core) return word;\n      const repaired = repairOcrWord(core);\n      return prefix + repaired + suffix;\n    })\n    .join(\" \");\n}\n```\n\n### 4. Update `normalizeOcrTitle()` to use dictionary-guided repair first\n\nIn `normalizeOcrTitle()` (currently lines 609-659), add a dictionary repair step **before** the existing blind substitution logic:\n\n```typescript\nfunction normalizeOcrTitle(raw: string): string {\n  let text = raw.trim();\n\n  // Step 0 (NEW): Dictionary-guided OCR repair — resolve ambiguous substitutions\n  // using word-level context before applying blind character replacements.\n  text = repairOcrText(text);\n\n  // Step 1: Strip trailing section markers (existing logic, unchanged)\n  // ...\n\n  // Step 2: Blind OCR substitution for words NOT repaired by dictionary\n  // (existing logic, unchanged — acts as fallback for unknown words)\n  // ...\n}\n```\n\nThe existing blind substitution in Step 2 still runs as a fallback. Words already repaired by dictionary won't contain OCR artifacts anymore, so the blind substitution will be a no-op for them.\n\n## Verification\n\n1. TypeScript compiles without errors\n2. `repairOcrWord(\"ARUGU1A\")` returns `\"ARUGULA\"` (dictionary match for \"arugula\" via 1→l)\n3. `repairOcrWord(\"B1ACKBERRY\")` returns `\"BLACKBERRY\"` (dictionary match via 1→l)\n4. `repairOcrWord(\"CH1EB\")` returns `\"CHLEB\"` (dictionary match via 1→l)\n5. `repairOcrWord(\"GRILÍED\")` returns `\"GRILLED\"` (dictionary match via Í→i, contextually becomes l? — actually \"grilied\" won't match... need to check). Note: \"GRILÍED\" → lowercase \"grilíed\" → Í→i gives \"griiied\" which won't match. The plan says Í→i but the actual fix for \"GRILÍED\" requires recognizing that Í maps to L in this context. **If \"grilled\" isn't found via single Í→i substitution, add \"l\" as an additional substitution for Í**, or handle this in the fallback.\n6. `repairOcrWord(\"HELLO\")` returns `\"HELLO\"` unchanged (no OCR artifacts)\n7. `repairOcrText(\"BEET ARUGU1A SA1AD\")` returns `\"BEET ARUGULA SALAD\"`\n8. Run the title-loop evaluation to confirm no regressions\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":572,"cache_read_input_tokens":33836,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":572},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"992d880b-e463-4199-be8a-c9ca68db2e09","uuid":"9d16fd80-4602-4373-ab8d-f97a2b107fa9"}
