{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018PdoJTFvjgUrXG8pR84NLc","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/24-b15aa30/tasks/task-04.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"992d880b-e463-4199-be8a-c9ca68db2e09","uuid":"bfa1b52a-c296-4a7b-bc11-aaca95733336","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/24-b15aa30/tasks/task-04.md","content":"# Task 04: Strengthen garbled-text detection\n\n## Summary\n\nAdd pipe-in-word and mixed Cyrillic/Latin script detection to `isLikelyGarbled()` to filter OCR-corrupted body text (Pattern 7).\n\n## Files to modify\n\n- `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- None (independent of other tasks)\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. Add pipe-in-word detection to `isLikelyGarbled()`\n\nIn `isLikelyGarbled()` (lines 206-265), add a new check. A word containing `|` (pipe) between letter characters is OCR noise (e.g., \"Sp|aszcz\", \"pa|ką\"):\n\n```typescript\n// Add near the top of isLikelyGarbled, after initial checks:\n\n// Pipe character embedded within words = OCR artifact\nif (/[a-zA-ZÀ-ÿа-яА-Я]\\|[a-zA-ZÀ-ÿа-яА-Я]/.test(text)) return true;\n```\n\nThis catches text like \"Sp|aszcz paіką do grubość-ci około 1 centyme-tra.\" which currently passes because it has enough vowels.\n\n### 2. Add mixed Cyrillic/Latin script detection\n\nOCR sometimes produces mixed-script text when it confuses visually similar characters across alphabets (e.g., Latin \"a\" vs Cyrillic \"а\", Latin \"i\" vs Cyrillic \"і\"). A line containing both Latin and Cyrillic characters is almost certainly OCR corruption:\n\n```typescript\n// Mixed Latin + Cyrillic script = OCR corruption\n// Cyrillic range: а-яА-ЯёЁіІїЇєЄґҐ (includes Ukrainian)\nif (/[а-яА-ЯёЁіІїЇєЄґҐ]/.test(text) && /[a-zA-Z]/.test(text)) return true;\n```\n\nPlace this check **before** the vowel-ratio check, since mixed-script text may have \"enough vowels\" from both alphabets combined.\n\n### 3. Where to add in the function\n\nThe `isLikelyGarbled()` function (lines 206-265) currently checks:\n1. Vowel ratio (30-50% expected)\n2. Single orphaned short words\n3. Internal case transitions\n4. Lowercase starting letters\n5. Mid-text sentence boundaries\n6. Multi-word garbled fragments\n\nAdd the two new checks as items 1a and 1b, right at the start of the function (after the initial `if (text.length < 3) return false` guard):\n\n```typescript\nfunction isLikelyGarbled(text: string): boolean {\n  if (text.length < 3) return false;\n\n  // NEW: Pipe embedded in words = OCR artifact\n  if (/[a-zA-ZÀ-ÿа-яА-Я]\\|[a-zA-ZÀ-ÿа-яА-Я]/.test(text)) return true;\n\n  // NEW: Mixed Latin + Cyrillic = OCR corruption\n  if (/[а-яА-ЯёЁіІїЇєЄґҐ]/.test(text) && /[a-zA-Z]/.test(text)) return true;\n\n  // ... existing checks unchanged ...\n}\n```\n\n## Verification\n\n1. TypeScript compiles without errors\n2. `isLikelyGarbled(\"Sp|aszcz paіką do grubość-ci\")` returns `true` (pipe-in-word)\n3. `isLikelyGarbled(\"paіką do grubości\")` returns `true` (mixed Cyrillic і + Latin a)\n4. `isLikelyGarbled(\"PLACKI ZIEMNIACZANE\")` returns `false` (clean ALL_CAPS, no artifacts)\n5. `isLikelyGarbled(\"Beet Arugula Salad\")` returns `false` (clean mixed-case)\n6. `isLikelyGarbled(\"Пирожки\")` returns `false` (pure Cyrillic, no Latin mixing)\n7. Run the title-loop evaluation — the \"Placki Ziemniaczane\" test case (Pattern 7) should no longer select corrupted body text\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
