{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Q8HncupWuzhgDKVNbZsEUA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01AXsuNhTd6qrGzuWz1C3jXS","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/24-b15aa30/tasks/task-05.md","content":"# Task 05: Candidate-relative position bonus and first-after-preamble boost\n\n## Summary\n\nChange position scoring from raw line position to candidate-relative position, and add a bonus for the first candidate after filtered preamble lines (Pattern 3).\n\n## Files to modify\n\n- `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- None (independent of other tasks, though benefits from Task 03's OCR repair)\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. Change position factor to candidate-relative position\n\nIn `extractTitleWithEmbeddings()`, the position factor is calculated at lines 772-776:\n\n```typescript\n// CURRENT:\nconst relativePosition = rs.position / lines.length;\nconst positionFactor = relativePosition < 0.5\n  ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - relativePosition * 2)\n  : 1.0;\n```\n\nChange to use candidate-relative position (position among candidates that passed hard filters):\n\n```typescript\n// NEW: Use candidate-relative position instead of raw line position\nconst candidateIndex = scoredCandidates.indexOf(rs);\nconst candidateRelativePosition = candidateIndex / scoredCandidates.length;\nconst positionFactor = candidateRelativePosition < 0.5\n  ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - candidateRelativePosition * 2)\n  : 1.0;\n```\n\nNote: `scoredCandidates` refers to whatever array is being iterated at this point. Check the actual variable name — it may be `candidates` or `rawScored` or similar. The key is to use the index within the candidate array that already had hard filters applied.\n\n**Important**: The raw `rs.position` (line position in original text) is still needed elsewhere (e.g., multi-recipe logic, structural heading detection). Only the position **factor** calculation should use candidate-relative position.\n\n### 2. Add first-after-preamble bonus\n\nAfter calculating scores for all candidates but before threshold calculation, add a bonus for the first surviving candidate when it was preceded by filtered preamble:\n\n```typescript\n// Detect \"first candidate after filtered preamble\" pattern\n// If the first N raw lines were all filtered (section labels, metadata, etc.),\n// the first surviving candidate occupies the structural \"title position\"\nif (scoredCandidates.length > 0) {\n  const firstCandidate = scoredCandidates[0];\n  // Check if lines before the first candidate's position were all filtered\n  const firstCandidatePos = firstCandidate.position;\n  if (firstCandidatePos > 0) {\n    // All lines from 0 to firstCandidatePos-1 were filtered/empty\n    const allPrecedingFiltered = lines\n      .slice(0, firstCandidatePos)\n      .every(line => {\n        const trimmed = line.text?.trim() ?? line.trim?.() ?? \"\";\n        return trimmed === \"\" || !passesHardFilters(trimmed);\n      });\n\n    if (allPrecedingFiltered) {\n      firstCandidate.score += 0.08;\n      firstCandidate.thresholdScore += 0.08;\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nPlace this **after** the scoring loop (around line 795) but **before** the threshold calculation (around line 903).\n\nCheck the exact data structures — `lines` may be an array of strings or objects with `.text` property. Adapt the code to match.\n\n### 3. Important edge case: position 0 candidates\n\nWhen the first candidate IS at position 0 (the common case), `firstCandidatePos > 0` is false, so no extra bonus is applied. This is correct — the position factor already gives maximum boost to position 0. The preamble bonus only fires when position 0 was filtered away.\n\n## Verification\n\n1. TypeScript compiles without errors\n2. For test input: `[\"FISH & SEAFOOD\", \"Halibut with Saffron Cream Sauce\", \"4 fillets halibut...\", ...]`\n   - \"FISH & SEAFOOD\" should be filtered (section label)\n   - \"Halibut with Saffron Cream Sauce\" becomes first candidate with preamble bonus\n   - Should be selected as the title\n3. For test input: `[\"Lato | Zupy | DLA 4 OSÓB | ...\", \"\", \"OGÓRKOWA ZUPA\", ...]`\n   - Pipe-separated line filtered\n   - \"OGÓRKOWA ZUPA\" becomes first candidate with preamble bonus\n   - Should be selected as the title\n4. For test input: `[\"CHICKEN PARMESAN\", \"1 pound chicken breast...\", ...]`\n   - \"CHICKEN PARMESAN\" is at position 0, no preamble bonus (not needed — already has full position factor)\n   - No regression\n5. Run the title-loop evaluation and confirm Pattern 3 failures improve with no regressions\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":572,"cache_read_input_tokens":33836,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":572},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"992d880b-e463-4199-be8a-c9ca68db2e09","uuid":"2afba84e-21b4-4ee7-bc98-f3c40392c3ce"}
