{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Q8HncupWuzhgDKVNbZsEUA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DoG2fNK9AwSfjGvtc6w7ex","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/24-b15aa30/tasks/task-06.md","content":"# Task 06: Title-absent page detection\n\n## Summary\n\nDetect pages where no title is present (OCR starts mid-recipe) and return empty instead of guessing a wrong title (Pattern 4).\n\n## Files to modify\n\n- `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- None (independent of other tasks)\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. Add title-absent detection logic\n\nIn `extractTitleWithEmbeddings()`, add an early check **after** building candidates but **before** scoring. The check looks at the first few non-empty lines to determine if the page starts mid-recipe (ingredients or cooking instructions with no title):\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * Detect pages where the OCR capture starts mid-recipe with no title present.\n * Returns true if the first N non-empty lines are all ingredients or cooking instructions.\n */\nfunction isTitleAbsentPage(lines: string[]): boolean {\n  const nonEmptyLines = lines\n    .map(l => (typeof l === \"string\" ? l : l.text).trim())\n    .filter(l => l.length > 0);\n\n  // Need at least 3 non-empty lines to make this determination\n  if (nonEmptyLines.length < 3) return false;\n\n  const first3 = nonEmptyLines.slice(0, 3);\n\n  // Check if ALL of the first 3 non-empty lines look like body content\n  // (ingredients or cooking instructions), not title-like content\n  return first3.every(line => {\n    return looksLikeIngredient(line) || looksLikeCookingInstruction(line);\n  });\n}\n```\n\nNote: `looksLikeIngredient` and `looksLikeCookingInstruction` are existing helper functions in the file. Check their exact signatures and use them correctly.\n\n### 2. Apply the check with a higher score threshold\n\nIn `extractTitleWithEmbeddings()`, after `buildCandidates()` and the `isTitleAbsentPage` check:\n\n```typescript\nconst titleAbsent = isTitleAbsentPage(lines);\n\n// ... existing scoring logic ...\n\n// After scoring, before final selection:\nif (titleAbsent) {\n  // In title-absent mode, require a much higher rawScore for any candidate\n  // to be accepted. This prevents picking up stray body text or adjacent recipe titles.\n  const titleAbsentThreshold = 0.10;\n  selected = selected.filter(s => s.rawScore >= titleAbsentThreshold);\n\n  // Also reject candidates that are deep in the file (position > first 3 lines)\n  // when in title-absent mode\n  selected = selected.filter(s => s.position <= 2);\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Integration point\n\nThis check should be applied **after** the threshold filter (around line 909) but **before** the multi-recipe logic (around line 1061). The `selected` array at this point contains candidates that passed the score threshold.\n\nIf `titleAbsent` is true and all remaining candidates are filtered out, the function returns `\"\"` (empty string), which is the correct behavior for a page with no title.\n\n### Expected behavior for the two Pattern 4 failures\n\n**Mushroom Risotto case**: File starts with \"Reduce heat and stir...\" (cooking instruction), followed by more cooking instructions. `isTitleAbsentPage` returns true. The candidate \"CARPACCIO DI PESCE SPADA + CARPACCIO WITH CITRUS DRESSING\" is at position 4+ (deep in file, beyond position 2 cutoff). Filtered out → returns empty.\n\n**Sweet Potato Salad case**: File starts with \"2 large sweet potatoes...\" (ingredient), followed by more ingredients. `isTitleAbsentPage` returns true. The candidate \"Salt and pepper\" has a low rawScore. Filtered out → returns empty.\n\n## Verification\n\n1. TypeScript compiles without errors\n2. For a test file starting with `[\"Reduce heat and stir for 20 minutes\", \"Add mushrooms...\", \"Season with salt...\", ...]`:\n   - `isTitleAbsentPage` returns `true`\n   - Result is empty string (no title forced)\n3. For a test file starting with `[\"2 large sweet potatoes, cubed\", \"1 cup mayonnaise\", \"Salt and pepper\", ...]`:\n   - `isTitleAbsentPage` returns `true`\n   - Result is empty string\n4. For a normal file starting with `[\"CHICKEN PARMESAN\", \"Ingredients:\", \"1 pound chicken...\", ...]`:\n   - `isTitleAbsentPage` returns `false` (first line is a title, not an ingredient)\n   - Normal extraction proceeds\n5. Run the title-loop evaluation and confirm Pattern 4 failures return empty\n6. Confirm no regressions — files that DO have titles are not falsely detected as title-absent\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":572,"cache_read_input_tokens":33836,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":572},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"992d880b-e463-4199-be8a-c9ca68db2e09","uuid":"c594089e-3c91-401d-9434-1cca22e4b5ea"}
