{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Q8HncupWuzhgDKVNbZsEUA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FUvkLPjWF25bYUm3Ej1nCx","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/24-b15aa30/tasks/task-07.md","content":"# Task 07: Protect compound titles from dedup and filter structural sub-headers\n\n## Summary\n\nPrevent compound titles (with ` : ` or ` + ` separators) from being removed by shorter-substring dedup, and filter \"MAIN RECIPE:\" prefixes and \"--VARIATION:\" sub-headers (Pattern 5).\n\n## Files to modify\n\n- `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- None (independent of other tasks)\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. Protect compound titles in the dedup logic\n\nThe dedup logic is at lines 1039-1052 and has a critical warning comment:\n\n```typescript\n// Line ~1040: \"DO NOT CHANGE THIS LOGIC — it has been incorrectly 'improved' 5 times\"\nselected = selected.filter((a) => {\n  const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n  return !selected.some(\n    (b) =>\n      b !== a &&\n      aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n      b.text.length < a.text.length\n  );\n});\n```\n\nThis removes longer candidates when a shorter substring exists. But it incorrectly removes compound titles like \"HERB ROASTED PORK WITH MUSHROOMS : PORK WITH CARAMELIZED ONIONS (VARIATION)\" when \"HERB ROASTED PORK WITH MUSHROOMS\" (from a \"MAIN RECIPE:\" line) is also a candidate.\n\n**The fix**: Add a guard that protects candidates containing compound separators (` : ` or ` + `):\n\n```typescript\nselected = selected.filter((a) => {\n  const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n  // Protect compound titles — these use explicit separators and the full form is intentional\n  if (/ [+:] /.test(a.text)) return true;\n  return !selected.some(\n    (b) =>\n      b !== a &&\n      aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n      b.text.length < a.text.length\n  );\n});\n```\n\nThis is a minimal, safe change: it only protects candidates with ` + ` or ` : ` (space-separator-space) — these are explicitly compound forms.\n\n### 2. Filter \"MAIN RECIPE:\" prefix lines\n\nAdd a pattern to `METADATA_PATTERNS` (lines 51-76) or `passesHardFilters`:\n\n```typescript\n// In METADATA_PATTERNS array, add:\n/^MAIN\\s+RECIPE\\s*:/i,\n```\n\nThis filters lines like \"MAIN RECIPE: HERB ROASTED PORK WITH MUSHROOMS\" from entering the candidate pool, preventing them from competing with the actual compound title.\n\n### 3. Filter \"--\" sub-header lines\n\nLines starting with `--` followed by text (like \"--VARIATION: PORK WITH CARAMELIZED ONIONS\", \"--WERSJA NOWOCZESNA Z CZEKOLADĄ\") are structural sub-headers, not titles.\n\nIn `passesHardFilters()` (around line 285-326), add a check:\n\n```typescript\n// Lines starting with \"--\" are sub-section headers (e.g., \"--VARIATION:\", \"--WERSJA NOWOCZESNA\")\nif (/^--\\s*\\w/.test(text)) return false;\n```\n\nPlace this near the existing structural checks (around the sub-section header / colon-terminated checks).\n\n### Important: Respect the dedup warning\n\nThe warning at line 1040 says this logic has been incorrectly changed 5 times. This fix is **not** changing the dedup logic itself — it's adding a protective guard for a specific, well-defined case (compound titles with explicit separators). The core \"shorter wins\" rule remains intact for all non-compound candidates.\n\n## Verification\n\n1. TypeScript compiles without errors\n2. Given candidates:\n   - \"HERB ROASTED PORK WITH MUSHROOMS : PORK WITH CARAMELIZED ONIONS (VARIATION)\" (compound)\n   - \"HERB ROASTED PORK WITH MUSHROOMS\" (from \"MAIN RECIPE:\" line)\n\n   The \"MAIN RECIPE:\" line should be filtered in passesHardFilters. Even if it survives, the compound title should survive dedup due to ` : ` protection.\n\n3. Given candidates:\n   - \"PIERNIK TRADYCYJNY + PIERNIK NOWOCZESNY Z CZEKOLADĄ\" (compound)\n   - \"PIERNIK NOWOCZESNY Z CZEKOLADĄ\" (substring)\n\n   Compound title survives dedup (` + ` protection). Shorter substring may also survive, but the compound title is not removed.\n\n4. `passesHardFilters(\"--VARIATION: PORK WITH CARAMELIZED ONIONS\")` returns `false`\n5. `passesHardFilters(\"MAIN RECIPE: HERB ROASTED PORK\")` returns `false`\n6. `passesHardFilters(\"HERB ROASTED PORK WITH MUSHROOMS\")` returns `true` (normal title)\n7. Run the title-loop evaluation and confirm Pattern 5 failures improve\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":572,"cache_read_input_tokens":33836,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":572},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"992d880b-e463-4199-be8a-c9ca68db2e09","uuid":"f7627730-91b9-450b-baa2-3ff1db5db78e"}
