{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Q8HncupWuzhgDKVNbZsEUA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TceoJ1g1TSfDTgMKgE89FM","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/24-b15aa30/tasks/task-08.md","content":"# Task 08: Expand cooking verb list and add bilingual layout pattern boost\n\n## Summary\n\nAdd missing cooking verbs to `COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS` and add a scoring boost for the bilingual `[FoodName]\\n[English Translation]` layout pattern (Pattern 6).\n\n## Files to modify\n\n- `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- None (independent of other tasks)\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. Expand COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS\n\nThe current regex at line 268 is:\n\n```typescript\nconst COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS = /^(beat|fold|stir|mix|add|pour|bake|cook|cool|remove|place|combine|whisk|knead|roll|spread|brush|slice|chop|dice|mince|drain|rinse|peel|grate|melt|simmer|boil|fry|sauté|saute|roast|grill|broil|steam|let|set|transfer|serve|garnish|arrange|sprinkle|season|preheat|cover|uncover|reduce|bring|toss|cut|trim|shape|form)\\b/i;\n```\n\nAdd missing verbs that appear in recipe instructions but are not currently listed. These were identified from the Pattern 6 failure (\"Scatter vegetables around pan\"):\n\n```typescript\nconst COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS = /^(beat|fold|stir|mix|add|pour|bake|cook|cool|remove|place|combine|whisk|knead|roll|spread|brush|slice|chop|dice|mince|drain|rinse|peel|grate|melt|simmer|boil|fry|sauté|saute|roast|grill|broil|steam|let|set|transfer|serve|garnish|arrange|sprinkle|season|preheat|cover|uncover|reduce|bring|toss|cut|trim|shape|form|scatter|score|pat|rub|skim|strain|heat|discard|rest|marinate|wrap|flip|turn|layer|stuff|drizzle|squeeze|zest|soak|thaw|freeze|chill|warm|toast|crush|pound|crack|break|separate|weigh|measure|sift|dust|coat|dip|dredge|baste|debone|butterfly|truss|shred|puree|blend|process|pulse|whip|cream|proof|rise|punch|divide|portion|assemble)\\b/i;\n```\n\nKey additions: `scatter`, `score`, `pat`, `rub`, `skim`, `strain`, `heat`, `discard`, `rest`, `marinate`, `wrap`, `flip`, `turn`, `layer`, `stuff`, `drizzle`, `squeeze`, `zest`, `soak`, `thaw`, `freeze`, `chill`, `warm`, `toast`, `crush`, `pound`, `crack`, `break`, `separate`, `weigh`, `measure`, `sift`, `dust`, `coat`, `dip`, `dredge`, `baste`, `debone`, `butterfly`, `truss`, `shred`, `puree`, `blend`, `process`, `pulse`, `whip`, `cream`, `proof`, `rise`, `punch`, `divide`, `portion`, `assemble`.\n\n### 2. Add bilingual layout pattern boost\n\nIn `extractTitleWithEmbeddings()`, add detection for the bilingual title pattern:\n- Position 0: short title (1-2 words, often a single foreign-language food name)\n- Position 1: English translation (2-5 words, mixed-case, not an ingredient or instruction)\n- Position 2+: section label like \"Ingredients:\" or \"Składniki:\"\n\nThis is a common bilingual cookbook layout. When detected, boost the position-0 candidate.\n\nAdd this logic **after** scoring candidates but **before** threshold calculation (around lines 795-900):\n\n```typescript\n// Bilingual layout pattern: [FoodName (1-2 words)]\\n[Translation (2-5 words)]\\n\\n[Section label]\n// When detected, boost the position-0 candidate as it's structurally the title\nif (scoredCandidates.length >= 2) {\n  const first = scoredCandidates[0];\n  const second = scoredCandidates[1];\n\n  const firstWords = first.text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n  const secondWords = second.text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n\n  const isBilingualLayout =\n    first.position === 0 &&\n    firstWords.length <= 2 &&\n    second.position <= 2 &&\n    secondWords.length >= 2 &&\n    secondWords.length <= 5 &&\n    // Second line is mixed-case (not ALL_CAPS, not all-lower)\n    second.text !== second.text.toUpperCase() &&\n    second.text !== second.text.toLowerCase() &&\n    // Second line is not an ingredient or instruction\n    !looksLikeIngredient(second.text) &&\n    !looksLikeCookingInstruction(second.text);\n\n  if (isBilingualLayout) {\n    // Check if a section label follows within a few lines\n    const sectionLabelNearby = lines.slice(first.position + 1, first.position + 5).some(line => {\n      const trimmed = (typeof line === \"string\" ? line : line.text).trim().toLowerCase();\n      return SECTION_LABELS.has(trimmed) || SECTION_LABELS.has(trimmed.replace(/:$/, \"\"));\n    });\n\n    if (sectionLabelNearby) {\n      // Strong bilingual pattern — boost position 0 candidate\n      first.score += 0.15;\n      first.thresholdScore += 0.15;\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nAdapt the code to match the actual data structures (check how `scoredCandidates` is structured, how `lines` is accessed, etc.).\n\n### Expected behavior for Pattern 6 failure\n\n**Golonka case**:\n- Position 0: \"Golonka\" (1 word, mixed-case)\n- Position 1: \"Roasted Pork Knuckle\" (3 words, mixed-case, not ingredient/instruction)\n- Position 3: \"Ingredients:\" (section label)\n- Bilingual pattern detected → \"Golonka\" boosted by +0.15 → clears threshold → selected\n\n**Cooking verb fix**: \"Scatter vegetables around pan.\" now matches `COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS` (via `scatter`) → filtered by `passesHardFilters` → cannot be selected as title.\n\n## Verification\n\n1. TypeScript compiles without errors\n2. `looksLikeCookingInstruction(\"Scatter vegetables around pan.\")` returns `true` (new verb \"scatter\")\n3. `looksLikeCookingInstruction(\"Heat oil in a large skillet\")` returns `true` (new verb \"heat\")\n4. `looksLikeCookingInstruction(\"Rest the meat for 10 minutes\")` returns `true` (new verb \"rest\")\n5. For test input `[\"Golonka\", \"Roasted Pork Knuckle\", \"\", \"Ingredients:\", ...]`:\n   - Bilingual pattern detected\n   - \"Golonka\" selected as title\n6. For test input `[\"CHICKEN PARMESAN\", \"Ingredients:\", ...]`:\n   - Not a bilingual pattern (first line is multi-word ALL_CAPS)\n   - Normal extraction proceeds\n7. Run the title-loop evaluation and confirm Pattern 6 failure improves\n8. Confirm no regressions from expanded cooking verbs (verify that legitimate title words like \"Heat\" in \"Heat and Serve Meatballs\" at position 0 aren't falsely filtered — `looksLikeCookingInstruction` requires ≥4 words AND starts with verb, so \"Heat and Serve Meatballs\" should be fine if word count is 4+; double-check)\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":572,"cache_read_input_tokens":33836,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":572},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"992d880b-e463-4199-be8a-c9ca68db2e09","uuid":"76386070-8177-48d5-9115-88b9e15a7a8a"}
